abstract: Though Senator Dianne Feinstein trounced Kevin de León in a primary, they will still face off in November, after party leaders endorsed Mr. de León, reflecting the power of liberal activists.
snippet: Though Senator Dianne Feinstein trounced Kevin de León in a primary, they will still face off in November, after party leaders endorsed Mr. de León, reflecting the power of liberal activists.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — The first rebuke to Senator Dianne Feinstein came in February, when the California Democratic Party delivered 54 percent of its convention vote to her opponent, Kevin de León, a state senator — just short of the 60 percent he needed for the party’s endorsement.

abstract: Democrats painted the Supreme Court nominee as an archconservative who would endanger abortion rights and health care and protect President Trump.
snippet: Democrats painted the Supreme Court nominee as an archconservative who would endanger abortion rights and health care and protect President Trump.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senate Democrats, facing an uphill struggle to defeat the nomination of Judge Brett M. Kavanaugh to the Supreme Court, opened a broad attack on Tuesday, painting him as an archconservative who would roll back abortion rights, undo health care protections, ease gun restrictions and protect President Trump against the threat of indictment.

abstract: Elizabeth Smart’s “Where There’s Hope” offers advice on moving past trauma. Books by a psychologist, a pediatrician and a mother add more perspective.
snippet: Elizabeth Smart’s “Where There’s Hope” offers advice on moving past trauma. Books by a psychologist, a pediatrician and a mother add more perspective.
lead_paragraph: The author had a chipped tooth. It ruined her looks, she thought. She had to interview someone for her book, and she really wanted to cancel. The interview subject was Mariatu Kamara, the young woman from Sierra Leone who wrote “The Bite of the Mango,” a memoir about surviving a civil war, rape, losing the baby that resulted from the rape, having her hands chopped off, making it to safety and finally leaving everyone she knew to seek refuge in Canada. The author thought about this, about why she was considering canceling and who she was about to talk to — and “shut up very quickly about my poor tooth.”

abstract: The White House misleadingly said Senators Kamala Harris and Elizabeth Warren, both Democrats and potential rivals to Mr. Trump in 2020, supported criminals and gangs.
snippet: The White House misleadingly said Senators Kamala Harris and Elizabeth Warren, both Democrats and potential rivals to Mr. Trump in 2020, supported criminals and gangs.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House used its official Twitter account on Monday to attack two Democratic senators who oppose President Trump’s immigration agenda, falsely equating their criticisms of Immigration and Customs Enforcement with support for criminals and murderous gangs.

abstract: More than 4,000 people were lynched in the United States from 1882 to 1968, according to the three senators who introduced the bill.
snippet: More than 4,000 people were lynched in the United States from 1882 to 1968, according to the three senators who introduced the bill.
lead_paragraph: The United States Senate’s three black members introduced a bill on Friday that would make lynching a federal hate crime.

headline_main: 3 Black U.S. Senators Introduce Bill to Make Lynching a Federal Hate Crime

abstract: In a bid to make Washington’s halls of power more diverse, the Senate is seeking to create a $5 million fund to compensate its interns, the first such organized congressional effort in two decades.
snippet: In a bid to make Washington’s halls of power more diverse, the Senate is seeking to create a $5 million fund to compensate its interns, the first such organized congressional effort in two decades.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In the past two years, DaQuawn Bruce received news — not once, but twice — that he had dreamed of since middle school. He had been accepted into two competitive internship programs on Capitol Hill, opportunities that swarms of students vie for every year.
